Reasoning: The paper deals with communication in radio networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The use of back-off strategies and the study of constraints on the dual graph model suggest a focus on information theory (cs.IT) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The investigation of the performance of these strategies in the presence of additional generality to the model suggests a systems and control perspective (cs.SY). Finally, the use of lower bounds and the characterization of algorithmic efficiency suggest a focus on data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
